        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(ui): preserve visible chat stream text",
        "body": "Opened on behalf of Onur Solmaz (`osolmaz`). Work is in progress until Codex review and CI are green.\n\nAI-assisted: yes.\n\n## Summary\n\nWebChat could show assistant text, then make it disappear.\nThis change keeps visible streamed text on screen when stale history or a terminal error arrives.\nThe remaining confirmed part of #67035 is a WebChat state-retention bug, not a local-model latency bug.\n\n## What Changed\n\nThe chat controller now treats visible streamed assistant text as something that must be preserved until real history replaces it.\nThat gives final, aborted, error, and history-reload paths the same retention rule.\n\n- Added shared stream-retention helpers in `ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.ts`.\n- Preserved visible `chatStream` when a stale history reload does not contain replacement assistant text.\n- Materialized visible streamed text into `chatMessages` before terminal error cleanup.\n- Deduped preserved stream text against later final/history assistant messages.\n- Strengthened mocked browser coverage for stale history during streaming and terminal error after partial output.\n\n## Linked context\n\nCloses #67035.\n\nRelated PR: #77418.\n\nThis follows the narrowed maintainer repro from `run_e7fc89b73ec0`, where composer preservation passed but stale refresh and terminal-error stream retention failed.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: visible WebChat assistant stream text disappearing after stale history refreshes or terminal chat errors.\n- Real environment tested: local OpenClaw checkout on macOS with mocked Control UI browser E2E using Google Chrome.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch:\n  - `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-gateway-chat-load.node.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-gateway.node.test.ts --reporter=dot`\n  - `PLAYWRIGHT_CHROMIUM_EXECUTABLE_PATH=\"/Applications/Google Chrome.app/Contents/MacOS/Google Chrome\" node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/e2e/chat-flow.e2e.test.ts --reporter=dot`\n  - `pnpm exec oxfmt --check ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.test.ts ui/src/ui/e2e/chat-flow.e2e.test.ts`\n  - `git diff --check`\n  - `pnpm lint:core -- ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.test.ts ui/src/ui/e2e/chat-flow.e2e.test.ts`\n- Evidence after fix: controller tests pass 96/96, adjacent gateway/chat-load tests pass 72/72, mocked browser E2E passes 12/12, format/check/lint pass.\n- Observed result after fix: streamed text remains visible after stale history resolves and after a terminal chat error.\n- What was not tested: true Windows IME input, live LM Studio/local-model streaming, and full production browser behavior.\n- Proof limitations or environment constraints: this PR validates the narrowed confirmed WebChat state bug with mocked Gateway/browser proof. It does not claim to solve every symptom from the original broad issue text.\n- Before evidence: Crabbox AWS browser repro `provider=aws`, lease `cbx_126c45468a1a`, run `run_e7fc89b73ec0` failed 2 of 3 checks before this patch.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\nI tested the controller rule directly and the browser path that previously dropped visible stream text.\nThe new regression coverage covers both stale history and terminal error.\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-gateway-chat-load.node.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-gateway.node.test.ts --reporter=dot`\n- `PLAYWRIGHT_CHROMIUM_EXECUTABLE_PATH=\"/Applications/Google Chrome.app/Contents/MacOS/Google Chrome\" node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/e2e/chat-flow.e2e.test.ts --reporter=dot`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.test.ts ui/src/ui/e2e/chat-flow.e2e.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `pnpm lint:core -- ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.test.ts ui/src/ui/e2e/chat-flow.e2e.test.ts`\n\nRegression coverage added:\n\n- Error events now preserve partial streamed assistant text before clearing stream state.\n- Error events do not duplicate streamed text when the server already supplied the same assistant message.\n- Stale history reloads keep active visible streamed text.\n- Stale history reloads materialize orphaned streamed text when no active run remains.\n- Caught-up history clears streamed text when it contains the replacement assistant message.\n- Mocked browser E2E verifies visible stream text survives stale startup history and terminal error.\n\n## Risks\n\nThe main risk is duplicate assistant messages.\nThe fix mitigates that by comparing visible stream text against assistant messages after the latest user message and by deduping exact display signatures.\n\n- User-visible behavior changed: Yes.\n- Config, environment, or migration behavior changed: No.\n- Security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior changed: No.\n- Highest-risk area: WebChat message reconciliation around stream/history ordering.\n- Risk mitigation: focused controller tests plus mocked browser E2E for the two reproduced failure modes.\n\n## Current review state\n\nNext action: run `codex review --base origin/main`, address any P0/P1 findings, then wait for CI.\n\nStill waiting on: Codex review and GitHub CI.\n\nBot or reviewer comments addressed: none yet.\n",
